CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 1, 1941, pg. 10, reads: "The Young, Young Set Celebrates With Little Lois Simms - If you think the young, young set doesn't have a good time, look at this picture. From rollicking James Henry Jr., sone of the Dr. and Mrs. James Henry, to the honored guest, herself, Lois Simms, daughter of Mr. and Mrs. Earl Simms, a grand time was had by all. The party was given by the Simms at their family residence in Sandusky street.  The guests were: James Henry Jr., Bobby Lewis, Doris Garrett, Earl Simms Jr.; Oliver Brown, Yolanda Candits, Rose Eleanor Jones, Clarina Candidts, Jeanine Henry. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of children wearing party hats at birthday party for Lois Simms, from left: James Henry Jr., Bobby Lewis, Doris Garrett, Earl Simms Jr., Lois Simms, Oliver Brown, Yolanda Candits, Rose Eleanor Jones, Clarina Candits, and Jeanine Henry, gathered behind table with birthday cake with ten candles, flowers, and party favors, in dining room of home of Earl Simms, Sandusky street
